The paper also involves machine learning (cs.LG) as it uses a learning-based approach to solve the problem. The use of artificial training examples and end-to-end training further supports this categorization.

Artificial intelligence (cs.AI) is another likely sub-category as the paper involves the use of machine learning and deep learning techniques to solve a complex problem.

Neural networks (cs.NE) is also a possible sub-category as the paper specifically mentions the use of neural network learning in the approach.

Finally, multimedia (cs.MM) is a possible sub-category as the paper deals with image processing and restoration, which is a common topic in multimedia research.
